From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: win32u: WM_MOUSEACTIVATE for top-level WS_CHILD, no synthesized WM_SETFOCUS

Fire WM_MOUSEACTIVATE on every click for a top-level WS_CHILD editor so JUCE
finishes its deferred-focus handshake. Folds in the re-port of held patch 021:
do NOT synthesize WM_SETFOCUS for top_level_child windows. The original 014
port synthesized it, but on a cross-thread JUCE 7 popup (X50II activation form,
TH-U rig dialog) that re-entered handleFocusGain -> bringModalComponentsToFront
-> cross-thread SetWindowPos and HARD-DEADLOCKED the plugin (audio included).
Real Windows does not send WM_SETFOCUS for child-window clicks unless focus
changes; JUCE manages popup focus internally and the click still delivers.
Reconciled with the popup host-frame migration: the main VST2 editor is now
WS_CHILD of a WS_POPUP frame (not the desktop), so it is NOT top_level_child.
For that shape, compare the root frame with the active root frame before
activating. X50's activation form paints inside child controls of the popup
host frame; repeatedly re-activating the already-active frame on child clicks
starts a JUCE async-message storm and prevents the matching button-up from
being dispatched.

diff --git a/dlls/win32u/message.c b/dlls/win32u/message.c
index a0eb097896b..db2d844a582 100644
--- a/dlls/win32u/message.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/message.c
@@ -2806,11 +2806,28 @@ static BOOL process_mouse_message( MSG *msg, UINT hw_id, ULONG_PTR extra_info, H
 
         /* Activate the window if needed */
 
-        if (msg->hwnd != info.hwndActive)
         {
             HWND hwndTop = NtUserGetAncestor( msg->hwnd, GA_ROOT );
-
-            if ((get_window_long( hwndTop, GWL_STYLE ) & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) != WS_CHILD)
+            DWORD top_style = get_window_long( hwndTop, GWL_STYLE );
+            BOOL top_level_child = FALSE;
+            BOOL active_root = (hwndTop == info.hwndActive);
+            if ((top_style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) == WS_CHILD)
+            {
+                HWND root_parent = NtUserGetAncestor( hwndTop, GA_PARENT );
+                if (!root_parent || root_parent == get_desktop_window())
+                    top_level_child = TRUE;
+            }
+            if (!active_root && info.hwndActive)
+                active_root = (hwndTop == NtUserGetAncestor( info.hwndActive, GA_ROOT ));
+            /* vstpoc patch 0038 (014-win32u-mouseactivate-ws-child, 11.9 port):
+             * allow WM_MOUSEACTIVATE for top-level WS_CHILD (VST plugin editors
+             * with desktop as parent), AND keep firing it for that legacy
+             * editor shape even when already active. For popup-framed editors,
+             * compare the root frame instead of the child hit target; otherwise
+             * a child click re-activates an already-active frame and can start a
+             * JUCE async-message storm before the matching button-up is drained. */
+            if ((!active_root || top_level_child) &&
+                ((top_style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) != WS_CHILD || top_level_child))
             {
                 UINT ret = send_message( msg->hwnd, WM_MOUSEACTIVATE, (WPARAM)hwndTop,
                                          MAKELONG( hittest, msg->message ) );
@@ -2826,7 +2843,27 @@ static BOOL process_mouse_message( MSG *msg, UINT hw_id, ULONG_PTR extra_info, H
                     /* fall through */
                 case MA_ACTIVATE:
                 case 0:
-                    if (!set_foreground_window( hwndTop, TRUE, FALSE )) eat_msg = TRUE;
+                    /* vstpoc patch 0038 + re-port of held patch 021
+                     * (no-WM_SETFOCUS-for-popups): for a top-level WS_CHILD we
+                     * do NOTHING here — neither set_foreground_window (it would
+                     * WM_KILLFOCUS the editor) NOR a synthesized WM_SETFOCUS.
+                     * The original 014 port synthesized WM_SETFOCUS to drive
+                     * JUCE's deferred-focus handshake, but on a cross-thread
+                     * JUCE 7 popup (X50II activation form, TH-U rig dialog) that
+                     * re-entered handleFocusGain → bringModalComponentsToFront →
+                     * cross-thread SetWindowPos and HARD DEADLOCKED the plugin
+                     * (audio included). Real Windows does not send WM_SETFOCUS
+                     * for child-window clicks unless focus actually changes;
+                     * JUCE manages popup focus internally
+                     * (Component::currentlyFocusedComponent). The click
+                     * (WM_LBUTTONDOWN) still delivers, so the popup responds.
+                     * Reconciled with the popup host-frame migration: the main
+                     * VST2 editor is now WS_CHILD of a WS_POPUP frame (not the
+                     * desktop), so it is NOT top_level_child and takes the
+                     * normal set_foreground_window path below — its caret no
+                     * longer depends on the synthesized message. */
+                    if (!top_level_child && !set_foreground_window( hwndTop, TRUE, FALSE ))
+                        eat_msg = TRUE;
                     break;
                 default:
                     WARN( "unknown WM_MOUSEACTIVATE code %d\n", ret );
